Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle. Rectangular stamp. Clay medium, dull brown; some large red inclusions.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.173, 25). Name Kastor. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0370.17.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1222)
